
Debuginfo packages:
Kernel should be compiled with CONFIG_DEBUG_INFO
Debug info is inserted into the executable.
An uncompressed kernel is also needed (vmlinux vs vmlinuz) for debugging.
(Optionally) debuginfo package can be downloaded fom distribution maker.

Tracing and Profiling:

	* strace

	* latencytop - requires kernel recompilation

SysRq Key
	* option  msut be enabled in kernel cfg
	* must be turned on during boot
	-> basically a keystroke handler
